Lagos State governor Babajide Sanwo-Ou on Friday announced the ease of the curfew in the state. Sanwo-Olu said the 24-hour curfew will be eased on Saturday but movement would only be allowed between 8:00 am to 6:00 pm. The governor eased the curfew at a press briefing after assessing the level of damage done on public and private properties since Tuesday night. Details later. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .